<TITLE> AL MPs demand Shibir ban </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 10 (bdnews24.com)Two senior Awami League MPs urged the government Wednesday to ban the activities of Islami Chhatra Shibir, the student wing of the rightwing Bangladesh Jamaat-e-Islami, for nurturing the "politics of arms". Suranjit Sengupta and Fazle Rabbi Mian made the demand referring to the recent killing of student Faruque Hossain, a pro-AL Chhatra League activist, at Rajshahi University on Tuesday, reportedly by Chhatra Shibir members. "As they are involved in politics of arms, they have no right to do politics. We have to take decision to ban the activities of the armed politics of Chhatra Shibir," Suranjit Sengupta, also the chairman of the parliamentary standing committee on law, told parliament on a point of order. "They must shun the politics of arms if they wanted to be in politics," he said. Sengupta said that Nizami had recently visited Rajshai and held meetings with the Shibir activists there. Fazle Rabbi Miah, another senior lawmaker of the ruling party, echoed Suranjit and said the brutality of the Shibir activists reminded the atrocities of 1971 committed by the Jamaat-e-Islami Bangladesh, a collaborator of the then Pakistani occupation force who had killed millions of innocent people during the liberation war. "We should give a befitting reply to their brutality. Their politics of arms should be rooted out from the soil of Bangladesh. "We need some guidance in this regard," said Rabbi, chairman of the parliamentary standing committee on government assurance. He also demanded a statement from home minister or her deputy on this issue. "I hope the home minister will inform the House as soon as possible," said speaker Abdul Hamid who was presiding over the session. Campus violence has flared across the country in recent days. On Feb
